  "summary": "Preinstall reconnaissance beacon exfiltrating host identifiers via DNS OOB",
  "details": "Package declares `preinstall: node index.js \u003e /dev/null 2\u003e\u00261` in package.json, silently auto-executing src/poc/index.js on `npm install`. That script uses child_process.exec to run `hostname;pwd;whoami` and `curl https://ifconfig.me` to collect the installer's hostname, working directory, username, and public IP, then exfiltrates the concatenated data as a DNS label to a projectdiscovery interactsh subdomain (`d9bd62bu6g119svvav70o3p9tymtrxkoj.oast.site`) via `nslookup`. Output is redirected to /dev/null so the installer sees no evidence of the beacon. The package name uses an unrelated scope with an inflated version (4.999.0), consistent with dependency-confusion PoC namesquatting.",
